cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with designing a data structure for processing shortest path queries in a graph with a specific fault-tolerant property. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.GT) to derive bounds on the number of replacement paths. Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the data structure, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
